The paper deals with approximability of covering problems on graphs, which are classic topics in theoretical computer science. The use of subdense instances is a relatively new and interesting direction of research, which is likely to be of interest to researchers in the areas of algorithms and complexity. The paper also mentions the use of a recursive sampling method, which suggests a connection to randomized algorithms and data structures. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), and cs.CC (Computational Complexity). The paper also involves combinatorial optimization, which suggests the sub-categories cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) as possible choices.
